			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I don't see what the big problem is...<BR>
<BR>
For those of you that are gasping at the price, well the service isn't for you.  This is a service for those who don't mind paying extra to get a different experience. I see absolutely nothing wrong with that.  It makes sense to me that to add alot of DYNAMIC content it'll take a much bigger customer service team for these servers.  It makes sense to me that each and every one of these customer service people costs the company X$/hour extra.  Plus extra server space.  Plus extra content teams. <BR>
<BR>
Now, you can pay your ten dollars a month and still enjoy your game on your server with your friends, nobody is taking anything AWAY from you.  <BR>
<BR>
For those that are talking about the bugs in the game still, I think they've said time and time again that they are completely different teams working on these things.  That same argument keeps popping up every time something changes with EQ, but really, it's not everyone in Verant that has the ability to fix bugs. <BR>
<BR>
In case you're wondering, I for one will be staying on Saryrn cause my friends are all there, and they're the biggest part of the game to me.  If they all decided to go to the new servers, I'd have no problem with forking over the 50$ canadian a month, because I feel I get at least that amount in worth of entertainment.  <BR>
<BR>
My two cents anyways.<BR>

				</font>
