				sure,nec pet lifetaps havent worked in a year.paladin spells cease,desist,and thunder of karana have been broken for some time now. graphics bugs.glitched binds ie you bind in fp,go to vel and bind in thurg,it throws you back to fp and gm tells you 'sounds like a bug,sorry we cant help'.people lose items,in the past month one friend lost donals arms,logged on and they werent there anymore,and another friend lost a whole backpack,and gm said 'sounds like a bug,sorry we cant help'.recent mass LD and connection probs,as well as that fun fun 'active char' message youre still getting for an hour after getting kicked off.paladin 39 spell divine vigor is the exact same 100hp buff as 53 upgrade divine glory.the recent bug with illusions and other forms not working properly.the way the F button targeting doesnt work as well as it used to (hitting f3 to heal tank and it targets a goblin corpse) pathing probs in several zones,god only knows when those great divide wurms are gonna learn how to turn corners. broken items and quests. zones such as vp<BR>
and pom still awaiting to be revamped. and to a smaller degree pets sometimes odd pathing that makes them wander off and bring friendly mobs back to you after they get lost following you, they musta stopped off to ask directions. falling through floors,or to the bottom of the world.as well as bugs with corpses that cant be gotten, recently tracked a corpse of someone who died on sister island in oot to the middle of the ocean on other side of zone,swam down to it,hit /corpse hotkey,and it says too far away,though its right in front of me.  the good times that come when you run past a zoneline but dont zone,like a friends corpse i retrieved from kc because he couldnt zone out,and died in back corner a nice ways past zone,making people zone thru to dl when attempting to get close enough to drag. <BR>
 and when people face these,or many other problems,only have to wait hours for a response,if they even get a response.the girls bugged corpse in oot was petitioned for hours with no answer.and of course if/when you get a response,its to the effect of 'sounds like a bug, sorry we cant help' but of course,these are your servers inhabited by the average person,be they teen,parent,married,unwed,single,divorced,dating, <BR>
living alone or with room mates,bf,gf,or alien symbiote.<BR>
 but on the new 'super' server,all problems are solved.the bricks are made of gold.rusted weapons are only 'slightly grunged' and all this for the low payment of 19.99 er 35.99 )<BR>
  the new weapons and quests are only a bonus,what youre paying for is customer service, because youre not getting cs on regular servers,even if youre in the zone cs at the time.<BR>
granted most companies in any form of business dont charge extra for customer service,but verant is a special company,high above us mere mortals, they require the extra strongarm er donations for their customer service.how can they afford payments on their mercedes without your income that woulda been payment on yours.not that i drive a mercedes,but a neon.go ahead,laugh it up, but 50 bucks a month isnt .75% of my monthly income,not like bill gates's post on previous page.<BR>
  point is,well i dont actually have a point. guess my point is if you can afford a 300% price increase to have your petitions answered, and think it feasible to pay a 300% price increase for a game,go for it,rocky.i personally could cut my spending and afford it,but i wont.triple price markup isnt worth it to me,unless they offer me a personal gm assistant and a cute woodelf secretary. and of course ill be flamed by the 3% of eq players that are professional athletes and company owners who wont miss the extra money theyre paying out,but that doesnt bother me.ive never been known to remain quiet from fear of retribution.the flamers have the right to speak their opinion,however asanine and belligerant it may be,just as ive my right to speak mine.its what makes freedom a great thing.<BR>
 i can also see some positives with it,such as giving ebayers their own server.cause i wont miss the lvl 50 enchanters that dont know what mez is,or the lvl 30 shaman that when asked to heal they draw a blank look,awaiting the mage to heal the tank.yes,the ebayers will have their own server now,thus saving me countless deaths to people who just bought their 55 cleric and i made the mistake of grouping with thinking they could pull their own weight.<BR>
 in closing,damn dont i ever shut up,we'll have to wait and see what problems this may cause with the regular servers.one forseeable has already been stated,that gms/funding to fix older bugs and implement new content will probaly now go to the new server,thus leaving the other servers in the bug ridden present state theyre in now,as well as meaning we wont see many changes/fixes until the first class are made cozy,and we get the crumbs they drop.ill continue to play as i always have,one foot in the grave,dealing with problems as they arrive.and ive played long enough to know better than to rely on verant customer service for any help,so it wont be much change for those of us that have made this conclusion.sorry to sound down on them,ive met a few,and i cant emphasize how small a number is few,good gms/guides that actually care about the customers and the game.granted they usually tell me 'sorry we cant help' but at least they do it in a nice way.but my opinion of companies such as verant will never change unless im given reason to change.those willing to sacrifice clientel to squeeze a few more drops of blood from each penny will never gain my respect.cheers,and safe hunting
