				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As a customer, I am insulted at the conduct of VI. It just shows even more that all the company cares about is how to make the most money (as if they're not making enough already)! If they want to add new features or content, it should come as an expansion pack or through patches since people are already paying them every month. But no...now to get the new stuff you have to pay more. 4x more in fact. Every month too. Verant sure does have a big head to think that players would fork over the price of a new game every month. Hmph. In my opinion, EQ reeks of being static and stale and the whole game is basically a grueling level treadmill. I mostly play because it's like a chatroom with graphics and extra goodies to entertain you while you socialize online. That's the real fun of eq. Not the game, but the people. Now if verant wants to implement new features, they should give it to all game players. And if Verant is so intent of milking more money off of players, then players maybe would pay an extra $5 for the new service. But now verant wants to separate their players into first class and second class customers with this new &quot;premium service.&quot; I never heard of a GAME that only allows players to access new areas and get new armor if they pay more real world money every month. EQ reeks of staleness already. I expect new features and customer service just to keep me paying my $10 every month. Why do I have to suddenly pay 4X more EVERY MONTH if I want those things? And where did this new &quot;premium service&quot; come from? Verant didn't have the time to work on Luclin or the bugs or the numerous other issues, but they had time to work on this? Shows where their priorities are. 
